            "class": "",
            "text": "\"Thou shalt not despise God, and the prince among thy people thou shalt not curse.\" Elohim does not mean either the gods of other nations, as Josephus, Philo, and others, in their dead and work-holy monotheism, have rendered the word; or the rulers, as Onkelos and others suppose; but simply God, deity in general, whose majesty was despised in every break of the commandments of Jehovah, and who was to be honoured in the persons of the rulers (cf. ",
            "children": []
